  "prompt": "How many Facebook victims were there in 2011?",
  "response": "In 2011, Facebook experienced several security issues and breaches, but estimating the exact number of \"victims\" can be complex since it relies on various factors such as the types of breaches and what constitutes being a victim.\n\nFor example, one notable incident that year was a large spam attack in November, where users were tricked into clicking malicious links, resulting in unwanted content being posted on their walls.\n\nHowever, comprehensive data on how many individual accounts were compromised or directly affected during these events specifically in 2011 is not typically disclosed in granular detail by Facebook. Overall, it is known that millions of users were exposed to various security risks due to these breaches and spam attacks.\n\nTo get precise numbers and details, you might need to look at cybersecurity reports from that period or statements from Facebook itself.",
